{{see|hegira}}
==English==
===Etymology===
From Medieval Latin [[Hejira#Latin|Hejira]] < Arabic {{ARchar|[[هجرة]]}} (''[[Hijra|híjra]]'', '[[departure]]', '[[exodus]]'), referring to Muhammad’s flight from [[Mecca]] to [[Medina]] in AD 622; from the verb {{ARchar|[[هجر]]}} (''hájara'', 'to [[emigrate]]', 'to [[abandon]]').

===Proper noun===
'''Hegira'''

# The [[emigration]] of [[Muhammad]] and his [[follower]]s from [[Mecca]] to [[Medina]] in A.D. 622 to escape persecution.
# The beginning of the [[Muslim]] [[era]], equivalent to July 16, 622, by the [[Julian calendar]] of the day.
#:''Since the Muslim lunar year contains only 354 days, A.D. 2005 is approximately equivalent to Hegira 1426.''

